High-Availability Kubernetes Infrastructure on AWS using Ansible

1. Project Objective
   To build a DevOps infrastructure capable of running an e-commerce application in a highly available (HA) mode using Kubernetes. This includes provisioning AWS EC2 instances using Ansible, setting up Docker and Kubernetes, implementing autoscaling, and ensuring secure pod-to-pod communication.

2. Tools & Technologies

* AWS EC2
* Ansible
* Docker
* Kubernetes
* ETCD

3. Implementation Steps

* Provision EC2 instances via Ansible.
* Install Docker and Kubernetes.
* Create Kubernetes Role and RoleBinding.
* Enforce Network Policies.
* Take ETCD Snapshots.
* Configure Horizontal Pod Autoscaler.

4. Testing & Results

* All nodes joined and marked Ready.
* Autoscaling triggered at CPU > 50%.

5. GitHub Repository
   [https://github.com/raktim00/Kubernetes-Multi-Node-AWS-Ansible](https://github.com/raktim00/Kubernetes-Multi-Node-AWS-Ansible)

6. Conclusion

* Fully automated deployment pipeline
* Scalable and fault-tolerant architecture
* Role-based access and secure networking
